;; Need defs — loaded by sim.defs into (:need db). Content, not code.
;; :decay is the amount a need drops per rare tick (~4.2 s @30 Hz). All three
;; share the old uniform 0.0125 rate so decay is unchanged; per-need rates are
;; now a data edit away. (0.0125 = old per-tick 0.0001 x rare interval 125.)
;; :seek-below is the threshold under which a pawn will act to satisfy the need
;; (food: go eat). Only food drives a behavior so far.
{:food       {:decay 0.0125 :seek-below 0.3}
 :rest       {:decay 0.0125}
 :recreation {:decay 0.0125}}
